      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start, but it's still a bit high-level. I need to be ready for the execs who aren't just talking about \"fairness\" but are getting into more controversial territory. \n\nSome of them feel like these programs ignore the reality of different cultural or social backgrounds—basically the idea that certain groups might not be as \"ready\" for high-pressure corporate roles due to different societal focuses or educational standards. \n\nIf a skeptic wanted to argue that DEI actually *hurts* performance by lowering the bar or introducing people who aren't a \"cultural fit\" based on their background, how would they frame that? I need to see the most aggressive version of that logic so I can prepare our rebuttals.",
